track_notes: Trip up follows an old road bed.  Trip back goes straight down. The summit proper is heavily overgrown with briers.

1.1 mile hike with 800 foot EG along logging roads and off-trail.  Plenty of park available at Park Gap (35.0621, -83.5635) along seasonally accessible FS Road 71 (4/1-12/31).  There is a trail marker for the Park Creek trail but you quickly diverge onto an old logging road.  If I recall correctly, you need to take a right at two logging road intersections before the final off-trail push to the summit.  The area around the summit is densely forested but there is a large clearing and campsite on the actual summit.
2.8 RT hike on an abandoned logging rd with moderate bushwhack through dense underbrush to a clearing near summit.
